if we do something wrong.

262
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:59,640
Then… are there no other alternatives
besides turning myself in to the police?

263
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:03,880
How about…

264
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:08,400
we go to the shop and look for the owner?

265
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:12,240
You'll apologize to him
and seek his forgiveness.

266
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:17,840
Are you sure he'll forgive me
and not call the police?

267
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:20,000
We must have faith in God.

268
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,920
God is gracious. God will protect us.

269
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:25,040
I'll accompany you.

270
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:27,120
We'll do the right thing together.

271
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:42,240
Sir.

272
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:43,840
Hello, sir.

273
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:46,000
Sir.

274
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,320
I'm sorry, sir. I was in the wrong.

275
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,120
I shouldn't have stolen your things.

276
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,880
I'll return this to you.
Please forgive me.

277
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:02,520
Sir, he stole this supplement
because his grandfather has weak knees.

278
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,200
He knows that it's very effective.

279
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:06,200
He wanted to buy it,
but he didn't have any money.

280
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:08,120
He stole it in a moment of poor judgment.

281
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,520
He really regretted his actions
after he went back home.

282
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:13,040
Could you give him
a second chance on behalf of God?

283
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:20,280
If you were truly remorseful,
you wouldn't have waited for a month.

284
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,920
- Ah Jiao, call the police!
- Sir.

285
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:26,600
Sir!

286
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:34,800
CENTRAL POLICE STATION

287
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:37,080
<i>The great artist</i>
<i>can't be touched by anyone?</i>

288
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:38,800
I didn't know you were such a tramp!

289
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:44,040
<i>I didn't think you were so filthy.</i>

290
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,760
<i>You're filthier than me!</i>

291
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:51,240
You even slept with another man.

292
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:54,680
You really disgust me.

293
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:58,960
POLICE

294
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,960
<i>I told you the truth about what happened.</i>

295
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,200
Why won't you forgive me?

296
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:06,320
You betrayed our marriage.

297
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,400
Can you give me another chance?

298
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:12,600
You're filthy.

299
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,400
Don't you dare touch me.

300
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:21,560
How did this happen?

301
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,600
You were supposed to help us!

302
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:23,800
Stop arguing with him, Grandpa.

303
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:25,560
I shouldn't have admitted to him
that I stole something.

304
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,120
So much for God being gracious.

305
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:29,600
Did he give me a second chance? He didn't!

306
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:02,040
Excuse me, are these your keys?

307
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:05,600
- I found them on the road.
- Thank you.

308
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,880
Are you Shaw May?

309
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,760
Shanwen's mother?

310
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,840
How did you know I'm his mother?

311
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:16,720
I'm his classmate Zhang Tingting's father.

312
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:20,000
I heard from Tingting
that you're a famous sculptor.

313
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:21,120
It's nice to meet you.

314
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:23,080
I'm Zhang James.

315
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,800
Shanwen is very artistically talented.

316
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,720
Tingting showed me his work.

317
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:34,600
It was very well done.
He's indeed your son.

318
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:38,720
You seem to have a close relationship
with your daughter.

319
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,680
We're all right.

320
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:45,400
At their age,
they just want to become adults.

321
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:49,920
What we can do is talk to them
and share more with them.

322
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:53,760
We try to play the role of a friend.

323
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:59,160
In my case,
Shanwen shuts me out completely.

324
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,080
He treats me as the enemy.

325
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:09,280
Perhaps, they need time to build up trust.

326
00:28:11,080 --> 00:28:12,760
Love is all about patience.

327
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:15,440
I'm sure Shanwen will feel
the love you have toward him.

328
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:20,560
- Love is all about patience?
- That's right.

329
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:23,480
Love is all about patience and gratitude.

330
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,600
Gratitude?

331
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:32,640
- That's easier said than done.
- It's not easy indeed.

332
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:35,320
That's because we all have expectations
when it comes to love.

333
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:38,640
When these expectations aren't met,
the love will slowly fade away.

334
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:43,680
I must have disappointed him greatly.

335
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:49,000
He hasn't addressed me
as "Mom" in three years.

336
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,720
I just greatly disappointed two people.

337
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:57,320
Sometimes, we can't grasp
the expectations people have of us.

338
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:58,320
This is very normal.

339
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:03,720
Do you know if Shanwen has
any friends at school?

340
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:09,040
I believe Tingting is his only friend.

341
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:13,800
She told me that
he mostly keeps to himself at school.

342
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:17,600
They only became friends after some time.

343
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:20,960
I hope she can help look out for him more.

344
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,040
That's not a problem at all.

345
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:27,720
What about this? Give me your phone.

346
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,200
I'll save Tingting's number in it.

347
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:31,840
You can call her whenever you need.

348
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:35,000
- Is that all right?
- Of course.

349
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:46,680
If it's all right with you,
I'll give you my number as well.

350
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:49,520
If Shanwen needs counseling,

351
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:52,600
our church runs a community care service.

352
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:55,360
Besides myself, we have
many other great counselors.

353
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,120
Thank you.

354
00:29:58,560 --> 00:29:59,520
Thank you.

355
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:06,440
Whenever a tragedy happens,
everyone in the family is affected.

