364
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,280
What's wrong?

365
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:21,120
What happened?

366
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,960
I fought with my mother.

367
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:29,560
Why did you two fight?

368
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:32,520
I blamed her for causing
the death of my older sister.

369
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,240
Actually,

370
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:49,680
I'm to blame too.

371
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,200
On the day my sister died,

372
00:31:56,800 --> 00:31:58,120
I didn't stop her.

373
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:01,840
- I didn't ask her to stay.
- Sun Shanwen.

374
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:04,800
Sun Shanwen, look at me.

375
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:10,600
Stop blaming yourself, all right?

376
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:20,000
I'm going home. This is annoying.

377
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:25,520
What?

378
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,000
On the day Cindy died,

379
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,800
why did she look for you?

380
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:34,600
The whole world
is asking me this question.

381
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:36,360
- I'm sick of it!
- Sun Shanwen!

382
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:41,800
She was my good friend.
I'd want to know, of course.

383
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,320
Okay. Since you really want to know,

384
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,960
I can tell you,
but you'll have to keep it a secret.

385
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:52,400
Again?

386
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:55,360
You know I really hate keeping secrets.

387
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:58,280
I'll be forced to tell lies.

388
00:32:58,360 --> 00:33:00,680
Do you want to know or not?

389
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,680
I do.

390
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:07,320
Cindy told me that…

391
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:09,960
she saw my mother…

392
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:13,720
I just saw your mother
enter a hotel room with an older man.

393
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:15,800
What did you say?

394
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:17,520
I don't believe you.

395
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:19,760
Come see for yourself
if you don't believe me.

396
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,800
I'll be waiting for you
in the alley in front of the hotel.

397
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,040
<i>I'll send you the address.</i>

398
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,200
Could she have seen wrongly?

399
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:30,440
My mother admitted to it
when I confronted her this morning.

400
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:34,120
How did she admit to it?

401
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:36,040
She asked me who I heard it from.

402
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:39,400
Sun Shanwen,
how is that an admission of guilt?

403
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:43,040
Auntie Ruoyun is so classy and graceful.

404
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:45,760
She couldn't have
done something like that.

405
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:48,240
Perhaps…

406
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,520
Cindy didn't see correctly.

407
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:53,560
Also, she had never met
your mother before, right?

408
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,120
I don't think so.

409
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,120
There you go.

410
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:01,040
Cindy always did things
without thinking them through.

411
00:34:01,120 --> 00:34:02,840
It's very likely
that she recognized the wrong person.

412
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:04,800
I really hope that…

413
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:09,120
her murderer can be caught soon.

414
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:25,800
- Let me walk you home.
- It's fine. It's not on the way.

415
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,880
Don't look for an excuse to not go home.

416
00:34:28,719 --> 00:34:30,400
You're always carrying so much stuff.

417
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,880
Hello, Auntie. I'm Tingting.
I'm Shanwen's classmate.

418
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:55,199
Tingting.

419
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,120
Have you seen Shanwen?

420
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:04,160
He left.

421
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:09,160
It's okay. Thanks for letting me know.

422
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:13,040
These must be heavy. I'll drive you home.

423
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,000
It's all right.

424
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,880
I have a direct bus home.
It's very convenient.

425
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,320
You're Shanwen's friend.

426
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:20,120
Don't be overly formal with me.

427
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:21,360
Here. I'll help you.

428
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,360
My dad and I love
exercising in the morning.

429
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,480
I love nature too.

430
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:34,720
Therefore, for the topic of "Happy Times",

431
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:35,880
I always choose to paint nature.

432
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:37,720
What did Shanwen paint?

433
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:42,640
He… has never painted anything.

434
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:46,120
However, he does other things.

435
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:48,440
He does everything but paint.

436
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:54,000
Shanwen is introverted
and keeps to himself.

437
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,640
I always worry about him.

438
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:58,880
I'm thankful he has
a good friend like you by his side.

439
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:00,960
Thank you, Tingting.

440
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:04,520
Don't worry, Auntie Ruoyun.

441
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:08,400
I'll keep buzzing
around him like a mosquito…

442
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:09,680
and tell him to treat you better.

443
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:21,600
Thank you for sharing
about Shanwen with me.

444
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,000
Don't mention it, Auntie Ruoyun.

445
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:25,120
Thank you for your guidance.

446
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:27,760
Feel free to look for me anytime
if you need anything.

447
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:39,600
Auntie Ruoyun, something dropped inside.

448
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:45,040
So, that's where it went.

449
00:36:45,680 --> 00:36:47,880
Cindy had the same bracelet.

450
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:51,840
Who knew that Cindy and I
share the same taste.

451
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:55,200
Such bracelets are common.
They're sold everywhere.

452
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:58,320
That reminds me.

453
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:01,680
Have the police found any clues
regarding Cindy's murderer?

454
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:03,720
I don't think so.

455
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:07,520
Otherwise, Cindy's mother
wouldn't be so upset.

456
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:08,680
She refuses to see anyone.

457
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:12,320
It'll take some time to heal.

458
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,920
Auntie Ruoyun,

459
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:17,680
could I make a presumptuous request?

460
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,320
Let's hear it.

461
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:21,920
Are you willing to meet Cindy's mother?

462
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:22,920
You could counsel her.

463
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:25,520
She said that
we don't understand her pain.

464
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,920
I saw the two of you hugging
in the bathroom the other day,

465
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:30,520
so I hope you can help her.

466
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:35,200
Auntie Ruoyun,

467
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:38,320
it's all right
if it's inconvenient for you.

468
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:40,600
Forget I said anything at all.

469
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:43,520
If you think I'd be able to console her,

470
00:37:43,600 --> 00:37:44,960
I'd be more than willing to try.

471
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:47,880
Thank you, Auntie Ruoyun!

472
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:02,440
<i>Should I publicize this recording?</i>

473
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:07,000
<i>It won't hurt me since I'm a widower.</i>

474
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:11,400
However, I wonder
what people would think of…

475
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,240
your family.

476
00:40:44,600 --> 00:40:45,720
What are you doing?

477
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:47,840
Did you take my things?

478
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:49,680
I did.

479
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:51,120
What right do you have to take my things?

480
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:53,320
- Why did you take drugs then?
- Why do you care?

481
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:56,640
You must quit taking drugs.

482
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:58,960
Drugs will ruin your life.

483
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:01,160
Did you take the high heel too?

484
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:04,200
Yes.

485
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:07,440
Cindy wore those before she died, right?

486
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,040
Did you meet her that night?

487
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:16,600
Why did she look for you?
What did she tell you?

488
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:22,080
What would have happened if the police
had decided to search your room that day?

489
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:26,640
Yes, I met Cindy that night.

490
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:28,920
Why?

491
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,920
The semen may not have been yours,

492
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:38,120
but if the police knew
you were there that night

493
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:39,880
and if they found
your fingerprints on the high heel,

494
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:42,200
you would become a prime suspect!

495
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,200
Shanwen!

496
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:51,320
Do you think that…

497
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:53,800
I killed her?

498
00:41:59,080 --> 00:42:00,800
As depraved as I might be,

499
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:03,720
I would never kill someone.

500
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:26,280
What's wrong?

501
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:29,600
I can't sleep.

502
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:35,200
Same here.

503
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:57,160
I haven't turned 18 yet.

504
00:42:58,120 --> 00:42:59,560
Your birthday is next month.

505
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:31,320
<i>Do you think that…</i>

506
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:32,960
<i>I killed her?</i>
